Peru Stocks: Austral, Cerro Verde, Maple, Relapasa, Siderperu

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-08-04T17:40:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/peru-stocks-austral-cerro-verde-maple-relapasa-siderperu.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:07 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index fell for a fifth session, dropping
3.5 percent to 20,756.23. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index
declined 2.8 percent to 2,606.73.  Industrial stocks slumped after U.S. stocks declined on
concern the economy is weakening, said Leoncio Altamirano, a
trader at Lima-based Juan Magot y Asociados SAB.  Empresa Siderurgica del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), the Gerdau
SA unit known as Siderperu, dropped 6 percent to 1.40 soles.
Austral Group SA (AUSTRAC1 PE), a unit of Austevoll Seafood ASA,
fell 5.7 percent to 33 centimos. Refineria la Pampilla SA
(RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain â€™s Repsol YPF SA known as
Relapasa, slid 4.4 percent to 87 centimos after crude futures in
New York declined for a fifth day.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  ,
the oil and natural gas producer with operations in Peru, fell
5.1 percent to $1.12.  Mining stocks dropped after metals declined in New York and
 London .  Rio Cristal Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian zinc
exploration company, plunged 10 percent to 18 cents.  Alturas
Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold exploration
company, fell 6.3 percent to 15 cents.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold exploration company, dropped 5.9
percent to 48 cents. Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1
PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., fell 4.6
percent to $40.35.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian
exploration company, declined 6.5 percent to $1.30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
